webexSubServiceType.description: this defines the sub service type

breakout.description: Details associated with a breakout move

breakoutLatency.description: Latency values associated with breakout session

identifiers.description:
Base type for the various identifiers used to connect the dots.
In general, these should be populated whenever possible. Subtypes may make a particular key required.

cpaasIdentifiers.description:
Set of identifiers dedicated to CPaaS clients
In general, these should be populated whenever possible. Subtypes may make a particular key required.

sourceMetadata.description: metadata associated with emitter of the event. This data is included only in the first emitted for a given call and does not need to be repeated with each event.

edgeInfo.description: Details of a media edge server which is in the media path but does not generate MQE directly

items.description: represents media quality event data associated with an interval

intervalMetadata.description: The metadata associated with the emitter of the event.  This data is separate from the source metadata and must be emitted with every event.

memoryUsage.description: this object defines the memory related fields that are tracked in media quality events and reports

cpuInfo.description: This object defines the fields related to the CPU being used by the emitter of the event

sourceChanges.description: This object tracks SSRC and CSRC changes for an RTP stream, session, etc

ssrcChanges.description: The number of RTP SSRC changes seen.  The first RTP packet seen should NOT be counted as a change.

csrcChanges.description: The number of RTP CSRC changes seen.  The first RTP packet seen should NOT be counted as a change.  Changes from zero to non-zero CSRC should be counted as a change.

encoderBufferPacket.description: The number of audio packets sent to the encoder buffer

encoderBufferDroppedPacket.description: The number of dropped audio packets before sent to the encoder buffer

averageBNRProcessTime.description: The average processing time (microseconds) on background noise reduction (BNR)

averageEncoderProcessTime.description: The average processing time (microseconds) on audio encoder pipeline

audioAlgorithmModulesInfo.description: audio transmitted algorithm modules performance data(AEC,AGC,NR,MultiChannelPreprocess)

aecNearPower.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

aecFarPower.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

aecLinearOutPower.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

aecOutPower.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

aecERLE.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 54dB, plus 1 indicate +0.5dB

aecERL.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0dB, plus 1 indicate +0.5dB

linearAecERLE.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 54dB, plus 1 indicate +0.5dB

estDelay.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0ms, plus 1 indicate 10ms

multichannelDelaySumOutPower.description: one unsigend char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

multichannelAverageOutPower.description: one unsigend char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

speechRMS.description: one unsigned char every 1 minute, 0 for 0dB, plus 1 for -0.5dB

speechLength.description: one unsigned char every 1 minute, 0 for 0s, plus 4 for +1s

speechQuality.description: one unsigned char every 1 minute, VAD value to reflect speech quality

bnrSNR.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 for 0dB, plus 1 for 0.5dB

multichannelDelaySumAndDirectMixRMSRatio.description: one char every 1 minute, 0 indicate 0db, plus 1 indicate 0.0472dB.

audioModuleQualityInfo.description: audio transmit pipeline modules' quality metric

aecNearPower.description: one char every 2 seconds. 0 indicate 0dB, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

agcAvgOutPower.description: one char every 2 seconds. 0 indicate 0dB, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

agcAvgInputPower.description: one char every 2 seconds. 0 indicate 0dB, plus 1 indicate -0.5dB

audioMeanVolume.description: The mean audio output volume for a microphone or speaker, in absolute volume [0-65535]

concealmentReasonByPacket.description: The object tracks the detail reasons by which concealment is caused. The unit of metrics depend on upper-level objects. Currently, packet or frame can be used as unit.

byOverflow.description: concealment caused by buffer overflow. when total buffer length exceeds max delay threshold, buffer will overflow and data will be dropped.

byReset.description: concealment caused by buffer is reset.

byLate.description: concealment caused by late packet or frame. some packets or frames arrive late and the previous one has been played.

byIncreasedDelay.description: only for audio. Number of concealment packets/frames sent to the audio decoder when frames are held back to increase re-order audio delay.

byAVSync.description: only for video. concealment caused by AV sync

byPrevFramePopped.description: only for video. Some video frames which have not been complete are forced to pop up because the subsequent frame has been complete. This cause video concealment.

byOthers.description: concealment caused by the other unknown reasons

concealmentReasonByFrame.description: The object tracks the detail reasons by which concealment is caused. The unit of metrics depend on upper-level objects. Currently, packet or frame can be used as unit.

interruptCount.description: the number of  consecutive concealment time which is larger than the threshold in one minute.  Currently,  60 and 120 ms are used as the threshold.

longerThan60.description: interrupt count longer than 60 ms in one minute

longerThan120.description: interrupt count longer than 120 ms in one minute

meanDelay.description: The average delay (in milliseconds) used by the jitter buffer

maxDelay.description: The maximum delay (in milliseconds) used by the jitter buffer

minDelay.description: The minimum delay (in milliseconds) used by the jitter buffer

endToEndDelay.description: This object tracks the the end to end delay(the delay between capture time of sender side and render time of receiver side)

meanDelay.description: The average delay (in milliseconds) from end to end

maxDelay.description: The maximum delay (in milliseconds) from end to end

minDelay.description: The minimum delay (in milliseconds) from end to end

endToEndDelayByCsi.description: Aggregated end to end delay representing the mean, max, min delay group by csi

items.description: This object tracks the the end to end delay(the delay between capture time of sender side and render time of receiver side) group by csi
